"""{{STORY_SLUG}} schema primitives (Story {{STORY_KEY}}).

All shapes in this module are the reviewable contract that downstream stories
read and write against. Pydantic v2.

Idiom checklist (see docs/dev-guide/pydantic-v2-schema-checklist.md for rationale):
    - ``model_config = ConfigDict(extra="forbid", validate_assignment=True)``
      on every model. ``validate_assignment=True`` is the fix for G6 MF-1/2/3
      (mutation re-validation); ``extra="forbid"`` catches typos at construction.
    - Timezone-aware ``datetime`` on every timestamp field via a
      ``field_validator`` that rejects naive datetimes (G6 MF-4). Use
      ``datetime.now(tz=UTC)`` as default, never ``datetime.utcnow()``.
    - UUIDs are validated as UUID4 format via ``uuid.UUID(v, version=4)``
      parse + re-emit as str (G6 SF-5).
    - Closed enums get three red-rejection surfaces: Pydantic validator,
      JSON Schema ``enum`` array, and a ``TypeAdapter`` round-trip test.
    - Internal audit fields use ``SkipJsonSchema[...] = Field(exclude=True, ...)``
      so Maya-facing ``model_dump()`` cannot leak them. Provide a dedicated
      ``to_audit_dump()`` for callers that need precise provenance.
    - Free-text fields (for example ``rationale``) have no ``min_length``;
      empty, single-char, and whitespace-only are all acceptable.

Discipline notes from R1 ruling amendment 17 / R2 rider S-3:
    User-facing strings in this module must present Marcus as a single voice.
    Keep legacy split-role terminology out of descriptions, docstrings, error
    messages, and companion docs. Private audit taxonomy is exempt.
"""

from __future__ import annotations

from datetime import UTC, datetime

from pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict, Field, field_validator

